http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/letters/Freed-for-%E2%80%98good-conduct%E2%80%99/article13986932.ece

Celebrities like Salman Khan and Sanjay Dutt appear to have more leverage in the system and over others who have to face the law and its consequences (“Sanjay Dutt to be freed on Feb.27 for ‘good conduct’,” Jan.7). It is quite evident that in our system, justice and equality are not being dispensed the way they ought to be. One can wryly remark that it all boils down to how famous one is.Ashvarya Sinha,Bengaluru